 :tx/rationale "THRESHOLD-TUNE PROPOSAL: The JOIN_THRESHOLD (0.65) was calibrated for hash embedder cosine distributions, not model2vec distributions. Hash embedder cosine is sparse (many zero overlaps, high values only when many words match). Model2vec cosine is dense (most texts have some similarity, values spread across [0.1, 0.9]). The threshold that separates 'same concept' from 'different concept' may need adjustment for the model embedder. APPROACH: (1) Before tuning, measure the distribution. Embed the 5 innate concept descriptions + 30 DOGFOOD-3 observations with model2vec. Compute the 5x30 cosine similarity matrix. (2) For each observation, check: does the highest-similarity innate concept match human intuition? What threshold separates correct matches from incorrect ones? (3) Expected outcome: model2vec should produce cosine > 0.5 for semantically related pairs (anomalies description vs error-handling observation) and cosine < 0.3 for unrelated pairs. The threshold may need to drop from 0.65 to 0.45-0.55 for model2vec. (4) Make threshold configurable via policy manifest: :policy/concept-join-threshold. The constant JOIN_THRESHOLD becomes the default when no policy datom exists. VERIFICATION: (A) Distribution analysis produces a clear bimodal separation. (B) Threshold produces >=80% correct concept assignment on DOGFOOD-3 observations. (C) Policy-manifest threshold override works."
